{"ts": "2026-06-09T17:03:00.181226+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:lVW9Wy | successfully downloaded text file (SHA: e0f90ac88e1236616df18600c7f7a5f80ac113c6)", "id": "lc_44de52c0-8770-4031-8708-d1c95db35ed0"}, {"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:lVW9Wy | from datetime import datetime, timedelta\n| MCP:lVW9Wy | from typing import Any, Dict\n| MCP:lVW9Wy | \n| MCP:lVW9Wy | from fastapi.security import OAuth2PasswordBearer\n| MCP:lVW9Wy | from jose import jwt\n| MCP:lVW9Wy | \n| MCP:lVW9Wy | from app.services import BaseService\n| MCP:lVW9Wy | from app.settings import settings\n| MCP:lVW9Wy | \n| MCP:lVW9Wy | # for authentication that works seamlessly with OpenAPI\n| MCP:lVW9Wy | reuseable_oauth = OAuth2PasswordBearer(\n| MCP:lVW9Wy |     tokenUrl=\"/api/v1/user/login\",\n| MCP:lVW9Wy |     scheme_name=\"JWT\"\n| MCP:lVW9Wy | )\n| MCP:lVW9Wy | \n| MCP:lVW9Wy | \n| MCP:lVW9Wy | def hash_password(password: str) -> str:\n| MCP:lVW9Wy |     \"\"\"Creates a hash of the password\"\"\"\n| MCP:lVW9Wy |     hashed_password = settings.PASSWORD_HASHER.hash(password)\n| MCP:lVW9Wy |     return hashed_password\n| MCP:lVW9Wy | \n| MCP:lVW9Wy | \n| MCP:lVW9Wy | def verify_password(plain_password: str, hashed_password: str) -> bool:\n| MCP:lVW9Wy |     \"\"\"Checks if a password corresponds to a hash\"\"\"\n| MCP:lVW9Wy |     password_is_verified = settings.PASSWORD_HASHER.verify(\n| MCP:lVW9Wy |         plain_password, hashed_password\n| MCP:lVW9Wy |     )\n| MCP:lVW9Wy | \n| MCP:lVW9Wy |     return bool(password_is_verified)\n| MCP:lVW9Wy | \n| MCP:lVW9Wy | \n| MCP:lVW9Wy | def create_auth_token(payload: Dict[str, Any], expiry: int) -> str:\n| MCP:lVW9Wy |     \"\"\"\n| MCP:lVW9Wy |     This handles the encoding of user information into a token\n| MCP:lVW9Wy |     that can be used. It is generic so as to accomodate access and\n| MCP:lVW9Wy |     refresh token.\n| MCP:lVW9Wy |     \"\"\"\n| MCP:lVW9Wy |     expiry_delta = datetime.now() + timedelta(seconds=expiry)\n| MCP:lVW9Wy |     data_to_encode = {\"expiry\": str(expiry_delta), \"data\": payload}\n| MCP:lVW9Wy |     encoded_data: str = jwt.encode(\n| MCP:lVW9Wy |         data_to_encode, settings.SECRET_KEY, settings.JWT_ALGORITHM\n| MCP:lVW9Wy |     )\n| MCP:lVW9Wy | \n| MCP:lVW9Wy |     return encoded_data\n| MCP:lVW9Wy | \n| MCP:lVW9Wy | \n| MCP:lVW9Wy | class UserService(BaseService):\n| MCP:lVW9Wy |     \"\"\"\n| MCP:lVW9Wy |     This class helps perform bulk of activities required by the corresponding API\n| MCP:lVW9Wy |     \"\"\"\n| MCP:lVW9Wy |     def a_method(self):\n| MCP:lVW9Wy |         \"\"\"\n| MCP:lVW9Wy |         Here, the use of `self.save` is demonstrated.\n| MCP:lVW9Wy |         Ensure to take out this method.\n| MCP:lVW9Wy |         \"\"\"\n| MCP:lVW9Wy |         model_instance = ...\n| MCP:lVW9Wy |         self.save(model_instance)", "id": "lc_3c02ee3e-2fa7-4b6d-898d-9b4975b81e23"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "04003dd7-af79-4618-9ec7-ec4bb3349ef7", "tool_call_id": "call_3c85437f9f3e445fb2e017b5", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T17:03:18.983797+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Based on my exploration of this FastAPI template repository, here's the main Python dependency and service stack:\n\n## Core Framework\n- **FastAPI** (with all extras) - the web framework\n\n## Database Stack\n- **PostgreSQL** - primary relational database (via `postgres` service in docker-compose)\n- **SQLAlchemy** - ORM (through `databases` package and `sqlalchemy-utils`)\n- **Alembic** - database migrations\n- **psycopg2** - synchronous PostgreSQL adapter\n- **asyncpg** - async PostgreSQL driver\n- **databases[postgresql]** - async database abstraction layer\n\n## Authentication Stack\n- **python-jose[cryptography]** - JWT token creation and verification (used in `auth/services.py` with `jose.jwt.encode`)\n- **passlib[bcrypt]** - password hashing and verification (via `settings.PASSWORD_HASHER`)\n- **FastAPI's OAuth2PasswordBearer** - OAuth2 authentication scheme (token URL: `/api/v1/user/login`)\n\n## Redis Support\n- **aioredis** - async Redis client\n- **Redis Alpine** - Redis service (port 6379) in docker-compose\n\n## Testing\n- **pytest** - testing framework\n\n## Infrastructure\nThe `docker-compose.yml` defines three services:\n1. **web** - the FastAPI application (port 11000)\n2. **postgres** - PostgreSQL database (port 5432)\n3. **redis** - Redis cache (port 6379)\n\nEnvironment variables in `.example.env` show the database name is `akatsuki` with a test database `hebi`, and Redis connects to `redis:6379`.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 703, "prompt_tokens": 8753, "total_tokens": 9456, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 345, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 7744}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "mimo-v2.5-pro", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "c351604334dc4f84a5b40c6a4636358d", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ead56-6255-7713-9b0b-d6f7d8c0d47b-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 8753, "output_tokens": 703, "total_tokens": 9456, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 7744}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 345}}}}]}}}
